news.title: KKR to buy Japan's Mitsubishi Corp-UBS Realty for $2 billion
news.para: KKR will buy MC-UBSR from Mitsubishi Corp and UBS Asset Management. MC-UBSR was founded in 2000 as a joint venture between the two companies, and is currently one of the largest real estate asset managers in Japan with 1.7 trillion yen in assets under management.

news.title: Structural assessment report by arrested professor termed Chintels Paradiso building unfit
news.para: In the detailed assessment report with pictures of the building and its map, the professor had said that the Ultrasonic Pulse Velocity (UPV) Test results of the Chintels Paradisco apartment building and other results were doubtful.

news.title: Sub-registrar among five booked for illegal registry of land in Gurugram
news.para: Sources said the registry of the land in Kadipur had been executed on the basis of a fake general power of attorney (GPA) and forged documents and signatures of the original landowner.

news.title: Indore: Drive to recover land diversion tax intensified
news.para: According to SDM Pratul Sinha, the tehsil office has put as many as three properties including that around 8 lakh square feet land of Samriddhi Park Colony, 10.648 hectare land of Vishal Agrotech India Limited and a property of Gyan Vigyan Krida Sansthan on sell through auction on March 26-28 for recovery of close to Rs 1 Crore of land diversion tax due on said immovable assets.

news.title: Guwahati civic body plans to collect dues from 2.4 lakh property tax defaulters
news.para: The urban civic body, which faces low revenue collection every year, has joined hands with National Urban Livelihood Mission (NULM), community resource persons and common service centres (CSC) in a bid to recover the dues from the defaulters.

news.title: Several properties sealed in east Delhi over tax defaults
news.para: “On Tuesday, the civic body sealed a shop at a mall in Karkardooma for non-payment of dues of approximately Rs 2 lakh. Apart from this, notices were issued to two shops in the same mall for non-payment of property tax dues of more than Rs 10 lakh,” said an EDMC official.

news.title: Nagpur civic body warns 138 owners to clear vacant plots of garbage, issues notices
news.para: “The NDS team issued notices to the owners, of which 128 reacted swiftly and cleaned the premises on their own,” said an official from the solid waste management department. The process to initiate action against remaining plot owners is in progress, the official added.

news.title: Capital verdict peps up realtors in Amaravati
news.para: Land prices appreciated anywhere between 40 per cent to 100 per cent in Amaravati area after the high court said that the state government did not have legislative competence to change location of the capital or to trifurcate the capital.

news.title: Telangana government earns Rs 567 crore from land auctions
news.para: The Hyderabad Metropolitan Development Authority (HMDA) conducted the auctions in Rangareddy, Medchal Malkajgiri, Vikarabad, Nalgonda, Mahbubnagar, Kamareddy, Jogulamba Gadwal, Peddapally and Adilabad districts.

news.title: Andhra Pradesh government building 31 lakh houses for poor, says CM
news.para: The chief minister made a statement in the assembly on Thursday during short discussion on housing programme. He said that the government had acquired 71,811 acres of land in the state which is worth Rs 25,000 crore.

news.title: Delhi: EOW books 30 firms, societies for fraud in name of land pooling
news.para: According to police, DDA is yet to authorise any project under the policy. “Nobody has any authority to collect payments in the name of the land pooling policy of DDA,” an officer said.

news.title: Indiabulls Housing allots over 30 lakh shares at Rs 234.05 apiece to FCCB holders
news.para: Pursuant to the receipt of notice for conversion of FCCBs, for a principle value of USD 10 million, the company on Thursday issued and allotted 30,25,126 fully paid-up equity shares at a conversion price of Rs 243.05 per equity share, to the holder of such FCCBs, the company said in a regulatory filing.

news.title: Niranjan & Surendra Hiranandani divide some joint realty projects in Mumbai region
news.para: ​As per the settlement between the two brothers, Niranjan Hiranandani will own 250-acre township in Powai, while Surendra Hiranandani has received 350-acre township project in Thane, they added.

news.title: Sebi sells properties of Ravi Kiran Realty India, its promoters
news.para: Vishodhan Developers emerged as the highest bidder in the e-auction conducted on February 14. The regulator has been auctioning properties of Ravi Kiran Realty India and its promoter in a bid to to recover investors' money.

news.title: U.S. housing starts rebound sharply in February; building permits fall
news.para: Housing starts jumped 6.8% to a seasonally adjusted annual rate of 1.769 million units last month, the Commerce Department said on Thursday. Data for January was revised higher to a rate of 1.657 million units from the previously reported 1.638 million units.
